<h1>Yoop.ly Privacy Policy</h1>

<p><i>Updated: August 2013</i></p>

<p>Summary:</p>

<ol>
	<li>Yoop.ly will not share or sell student or teacher information with third parties without written authorization form school or district administrators.</li>
	<li>Yoop.ly will collect and store student information securely in compliance with FERPA regulations.</li>
	<li>Yoop.ly uses industry-standards encryption of all data traffic to prevent misuse of confidential data.</li>
</ol>

<p>Keeping school and student data safe is a priority for Yoop.ly ("we", "us", or "our") and our partner schools.  Our privacy policy below outlines the steps we are taking to make sure user and visitor data is secured. Please refer to our Terms of Services, which also incorporates this Privacy Policy.</p>
<p>By visiting Yoop.ly's  website at yoop.ly or any of our other websites, applications, domain names or other linked pages, (collectively the "Website"), or using any of our services("Services"), you acknowledge that you accept the practices and policies outlined in this Privacy Policy. By using the Website, you are also consenting to have your personal data transferred to and processed in the United States.</p>
<p>If you are not in full agreement with this Policy, please delete all cookies from your browser cache after visiting our Website and refrain from visiting our Website or using our Services in the future. Continued use of our Website or Services by you, your school, or agency will indicate your acceptance of this Policy.</p>
<p>This Privacy Policy explains how Yoop.ly collects and uses information from its users who access the Website and use our services, including Yoop.ly's treatment of personally identifiable information ("Personal Information"). Also, this Privacy Policy covers our treatment of any Personal Information that our  business partners share with Yoop.ly, or that you provide to Yoop.ly through a third party website.</p>

<h2>What is CHILDREN'S PERSONAL INFORMATION?</h2>
<p>If you are a minor (under the age of 18), you may only use this service and disclose Personal Information with your parent or guardian's express consent. Yoop.ly collects limited Personal Information from students ("Children's Personal Information"), but only where that student's school, district, and/or teacher has contracted with Yoop.ly to collect Children's Personal Information from students for the use and benefit of the learning environment. Yoop.ly requires schools, districts, and/or teachers to obtain parental consent from students' parents before collecting any such Children's Personal Information.</p>

<h2>What is PERSONAL INFORMATION?</h2>
<p>Hereinafter, references to "Personal Information" shall apply to personal information of individual Website users who are not student registrants. References to "Children's Personal Information" shall only apply to personal information of student users of the Website. General references to "information" shall apply to all users.</p>

<h2>How do we COLLECT YOUR DATA?</h2>
<p>Yoop.ly collects data three main ways:</p>
<ol>
	<li>Through cookies when you visit our website. Cookies are alphanumeric identifiers that we transfer to your computer's hard drive through your browser to enable our systems to recognize your browser and tell us how and when pages in our site are visited and by how many people.<br /><br />
			Most browsers have an option for turning off the cookie feature, which will prevent your browser from accepting new cookies. Yoop.ly recommends that you leave the cookies activated, as you will not be allowed to log in or perform many funcitons on our Website with cookies turned off.</li>
	<li>Through Personal Information you choose to share with us. By creating accounts, logging in, sending email to our domain, we are collecting your name, email address, username information and email content you share with us. We do not store nor are we aware of passwords created by users.</li>
	<li>Through Children's Personal Information and Personal Information your school, district, Student Information System, or agency agrees to share with us on your behalf and with your expressed agreement. By signing a contract with Yoop.ly you agree to share the following student and staff information: first and last name; class roster information including teacher(s) and class name(s), usernames; demographic data inlcuding race, ethnicity, age, socio-economic status; parent contact information including email address and phone number(s) of parents or guardians. We may collect this data through Third Party Software clients or agents with whom you, your school, agency, district, has already contracted with to provide you with Student Information System Services. Yoop.ly may pull information from these Third Party Sofware clients as part of any contractual agreement that is signed with a school, district, managment organization or entity that represents the user.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Protection of information</h2>
<p>Yoop.ly maintains strict administrative, technical and physical procedures to protect information stored in our servers, which are located in the United States. Access to information is limited (through user/password credentials and software systems) to those employees who require it to perform their job functions. We use industry-standard Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption technology to safeguard the account registration process and sign-up information. Other security safeguards include but are not limited to data encryption, firewalls, and physical access controls to building and files.</p>
<p>Yoop.ly  complies with relevant provisions of the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA), 20 U.S.C. 1232g</p>
<p>Yoop.ly will not sell,  nor commerce with, any Personal Information or Children's Personal Information with any Thrid Party Sofware providers or entities.</p>



